headline: Spencer Jakab | What Black Friday Does—And Doesn't—Tell Us About the Economy
summary: ? This is an online version of my Markets A.M. newsletter.  Watching the scrum on Black Friday has never been the best way to take the economy’s temperature, but it might be especially misleading this year.  “Well, I think this is the longest downturn of my career for 31 years, I think maybe the longest downturn…in our company's history,” said Shelley Simpson, chief executive at logistics firm J.B. Hunt, at a recent conference.
